ince a continuously-improving process is not necessary to establish control objectives as the basis for the selection, implementation and management of the organization','','','','','APO01.04 DSS06.01','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','CTRL:SG1.SP1','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','Added new control.','','',''),(12,12,'Asset Management','Asset Governance ','AST-01','Mechanisms exist to facilitate an IT Asset Management (ITAM) program to implement and manage asset management controls.','- Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP) - ITIL - Configuration Management Database (CMDB) - IT Asset Management (ITAM) Program','Does the organization facilitate the implementation of asset management controls?','10','Identify','- There is no evidence of a capability to facilitate an IT Asset Management (ITAM) Program to implement and manage Asset Management controls.','- Asset management is informally assigned as an additional duty to existing IT or cybersecurity personnel. - Inventory of physical technology assets covers common devices (e.g., laptops, workstations and servers). - Inventory is conducted at least annually.','- IT asset management requirements for security and privacy are identified and documented. - Controls are assigned to sensitive assets to comply with specific compliance requirements for asset management. - Asset management is formally assigned as an additional duty to existing IT or cybersecurity personnel. - Inventory of physical technology assets covers common devices (e.g., laptops, workstations and servers). - Inventory is conducted at least annually.','- An IT Asset Management (ITAM) program, or similar function, governs asset management that ensures compliance with requirements for asset management. - ITAM leverages an established Configuration Management Database (CMDB), or similar tool, as the authoritative source of IT assets. - ITAM function is formally assigned with defined roles and associated responsibilities. - The process of purchasing, updating, repairing and disposing of assets is integrated into ITAM processes - Inventory of IT assets covers both physical and virtual assets to create a holistic visibility into the organization\'s assets. - Inventories are configured to be recurring scans, based on the IT Asset Management (ITAM) tool configuration settings.','- Metrics are developed that provide management oversight to ensure the process is operating in an optimal capacity. - Metrics reporting includes this process so it can be quantitatively analyzed. - An IT Asset Management (ITAM) program, or similar function, governs asset management that ensures compliance with requirements for asset management. - ITAM leverages an established Configuration Management Database (CMDB), or similar tool, as the authoritative source of IT assets. - ITAM function is formally assigned with defined roles and associated responsibilities. - The process of purchasing, updating, repairing and disposing of assets is integrated into ITAM processes. - Inventory of IT assets covers both physical and virtual assets to create a holistic visibility into the organization\'s assets. - Inventories are configured to be recurring scans, based on the IT Asset Management (ITAM) tool configuration settings. ','- Predictive analysis (e.g., machine learning, AI, etc.) is used to identify and alert on trends to enable decision makers to make time-critical decisions at the speed of relevance to support operational efficiency. - Proactive adjustments are made to govern the process, based on metrics. - An IT Asset Management (ITAM) program, or similar function, governs asset management that ensures compliance with requirements for asset management. - ITAM leverages an established Configuration Management Database (CMDB), or similar tool, as the authoritative source of IT assets. - ITAM function is formally assigned with defined roles and associated responsibilities. - The process of purchasing, updating, repairing and disposing of assets is integrated into ITAM processes. - Inventory of IT assets covers both physical and virtual assets to create a holistic visibility into the organization\'s assets. - Inventories are configured to be recurring scans, based on the IT Asset Management (ITAM) tool configuration settings.','','','','1.4 1.5 2.6','BAI09.01 BAI09.02 BAI09.03 BAI09.04 BAI09.05','','','','SO15','','','','','','','','','','PS-12.0 PS-12.1 PS-12.6 PS-14.1 PS-14.2 DS-12.3','','PR.DS-P3','','P-18','','PM-5','','','','PM-5','PM-5 ','','','','','','','12.3.3 12.3.4 12.3.7 ','','','ADM:SG1.SP1 ADM:SG3.SP2 TM:SG1.SP1','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','5.S.A','5.M.A','5.M.A 2.L.A','','120.45','','8-311','','','','','','1798.81.5(b)','','','','','','','','','','','','Art 32.1 Art 32.2','','Sec 14 Sec 15','Art 16','','','','','','AM-03','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','','X','X','X','','','','X','Wordsmithed the control description.','Updated for Jan 1 2020 version of CCPA','',''),(13,13,'Asset Management','Asset-Service Dependencies','AST-01.1','Mechanisms exist to identify and assess the security of technology assets that support more than one critical business function. ','','Does the organization identify and assess the security of technology assets that support more than one critical business function? ','5','Identify','- There is no evidence of a capability to identify and assess the Security of technology assets that support more than one critical business function.','SP-CMM1 is N/A, since a structured process is required to identify and assess the security of technology assets that support more than one critical business function. ','- IT asset management requirements for security and privacy are identified and documented. - Controls are assigned to sensitive assets to comply with specific compliance requirements for asset management. - Asset management is formally assigned as an additional duty to existing IT or cybersecurity personnel. - Inventory of physical technology assets covers common devices (e.g., laptops, workstations and servers). - Inventory is conducted at least annually. - For critical business services and assets, dependencies are reviewed for security concerns.','- An IT Asset Management (ITAM) program, or similar function, governs asset management that ensures compliance with requirements for asset management. - ITAM leverages an established Configuration Management Database (CMDB), or similar tool, as the authoritative source of IT assets. - ITAM function is formally assigned with defined roles and associated responsibilities. - The process of purchasing, updating, repairing and disposing of assets is integrated into ITAM processes. - Inventory of IT assets covers both physical and virtual assets to create a holistic visibility into the organization\'s assets. - Inventories are configured to be recurring scans, based on the IT Asset Management (ITAM) tool configuration settings. - The CMDB, or similar tool, is leveraged to identify asset-service dependencies that can impact the security of technology assets.','- Metrics are developed that provide management oversight to ensure critical asset-service dependencies are identified and managed to reduce risk.  - Metrics reporting includes this process so it can be quantitatively analyzed. - An IT Asset Management (ITAM) program, or similar function, governs asset management that ensures compliance with requirements for asset management. - ITAM leverages an established Configuration Management Database (CMDB), or similar